      "transcript": "Claudia's got me over 6,000 new followers on Instagram through a single video.\nWe're back with Claude Runs My Life here to talk about how can help you with video scripts.\nOver the last few months, I've been studying creators and not just creators in the technology space.\nI look for people who tell stories and interesting ways and are able to engage people\nin ways that, frankly, I can't. The whole point of this is I wanted to use their techniques to\ntalk about the topics that I care about and Claude helped me do this so efficiently.\nI want to share with you three ways that Claude helped me write a script that got me over\n300,000 views across TikTok and Instagram. The first thing I did was use the Claude browser app.\nI had Claude go to all the creators that I was interested in across Instagram and TikTok.\nAnd then I had it look at all the most recent posts and look at the entire script and tell me\nwhat exactly were they doing for their hooks? How did their thumbnails look? What were some of the\nthings that they were saying? How were they phrasing content and structuring their content?\nSo it built me a style guide based off of all of these creators. Step two was telling Claude\neverything about me. So if you look back a couple of videos on my profile, you'll find something\naround how you created about me and a voice document that Claude can use. I did this and then I\nalso created a social strategy document for it to use where I describe the person who I want to\nget value from my content and what I'm specifically going to talk about. Step three was the biggest\ngame changer of them all. So step one took all the best practices from creators and step two\ntook my voice in tone and then I would put in my idea first script. Claude would create that\nscript but I wasn't done there. I would ask Claude to rewrite the script 10 times with the ideal\nperson visiting my profile in mind. So what it would do is it would rewrite the script and show me\nthat script again and again 10 times optimizing each piece of content for the person I was\nrelying the content to so they would best absorb the content. And what I found is each iteration just\ngot better and better and better. The final thing I will say with this is I do riff. So when I think\nabout a script it's really the bones. It's the structure. It's not exactly what I'm going to say\nverbatim. I think that the riffing actually adds a lot of personality. So Claude will give you the best\nmost optimized script but you don't want it to be like you're reading from a teleprompter. So save this\nvideo and if you want me to share my personal style guide and goals for my videos let me know\nand I'll do a video on that."
