      "hasScreenshots": true,
      "hasAudio": true,
      "transcript": "I got three job offers and four months, and I'm going to tell you all the weird things I did to get my application past the box.\nThing one, you've probably heard before, I copy and paste the job description at the bottom of my resume.\nI changed the font color to white, save it as a PDF, and apply it with that.\nThe reason is because a lot of these application portals are scraping your resume to see how much of a percentage match it is to the drop description.\nSo if you have a job description, paste it into your resume and hide it with the font color, then save it as a PDF, it actually works pretty well.\nNow, instead of doing all that extra stuff people tell you to do, I actually tested which job boards were even worth my time.\nIndeed, zero responses, like nothing.\nLinkedIn, I thought this would be better, but I only got like one response in two months to wild.\nWell, found it was a bit better, I got a few responses and a couple interviews.\nBut then I tried something completely different, globalwork.au.\nI uploaded my resume, I set the filters, I picked remote roles, and I turned on the auto apply only feature.\nI applied it two or three of these jobs manually first, so the AI could learn how I apply.\nAfter that, I literally started applying to dozens of jobs for me automatically.\nSo instead of sitting there refreshing the job boards all day, it was sending out applications in the background.\nIt's as simple as that."
