      "hasScreenshots": true,
      "hasAudio": true,
      "transcript": "Anthropic just dropped cloud co-work, which is basically cloud code for non-technical people.\nBasically, a general purpose AI co-worker that can do a lot of what a human can do with a computer,\nbut faster and without you babysitting it. It can clean up your files, like renaming,\nsorting, and restructuring messy folders. It can take scattered notes across files and produce\na clean document. There's even cross file edits where you can update and format multiple documents at\nonce, or you can even convert screenshots or PDFs into a spreadsheet. All while connecting it\nto tools like Google Drive and Slack. You give it access to one folder, tell it what you want\nin natural language, and then walk away, and co-work is able to make a plan, execute, and keep you posted.\nYou can also queue up multiple tasks and jump in midway or add new instructions while it's working.\nSo much more like delegating to a real teammate. Right now, it is still in research preview, so there are\nsome caveats. Vague prompts can cause unintended actions, and prompt injection is still a pretty\nbig risk with any agent that can take actions. But if you do want to try it, it is available for\nCloud Mac subscribers on Mac OS. I'm pretty excited to test it. If you've tried to work,\nI'm curious for thoughts and reactions."
